        {
            "_id": "OtWQPO05M1MuYUft",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Passive.webp",
            "name": "Slosh",
            "sort": 600000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "passive"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>Whenever the cranium preserver ends a Stride, the movement causes necrotic embalming fluid and preserved body parts to slosh about and spill from its central vat. Each creature adjacent to the cranium preserver when it finishes its Stride must attempt a @Check[type:will|dc:26] save.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature takes @Damage[1d8[mental],1d8[void]]{1d8 mental damage and 1d8 void damage}.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes @Damage[2d8[mental],2d8[void]]{2d8 mental damage and 2d8 void damage}.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature takes @Damage[4d8[mental],4d8[void]]{4d8 mental and 4d8 void damage}. If the creature is alive, the preserved body parts sense the presence of a living creature and cling to it, causing the creature to become @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Clumsy]{Clumsy 2} for 1 round.</p>"
                },
